title: Dell PowerVault ME5: Snapshots
agents: dell_powervault_me5
catalog: hw/storagehw/dell
license: GPLv2
distribution: Sher Zaman
description:
 Monitors the snapshots of a Dell PowerVault ME5 system, grouped by the source
 volume they were taken from. Reports the snapshot count, the total snapshot
 data and the age of the newest snapshot.

 Optional upper levels on the newest snapshot age detect a stalled snapshot
 schedule, alerting when no new snapshot has been taken within the configured
 time (for example 26 hours warning and 50 hours critical for a daily
 schedule). This is off by default because snapshot schedules vary.

 The source volume is resolved from the snapshot parent, so discovery works on
 any array regardless of snapshot naming. State is taken from the snapshot
 health value reported by the array. Conditions are configurable via the "Dell
 PowerVault ME5 snapshots" ruleset.

item:
 The source volume name.

discovery:
 One service is created per source volume that has snapshots.
